  "name": {
    "en": "Jackfruit Scones",
    "local_name": "Maandazi ya Fenesi"
  },
  "description": "Tender, buttery scones packed with sweet, tropical chunks of ripe jackfruit. These scones are lightly sweetened, with a fluffy interior and a slightly crisp exterior, making for a perfect breakfast or tea-time treat.",
  "origin_region": "Nationwide (Modern Fusion Baking)",
  "cultural_significance": {
    "importance": "modern_fusion_baked_good",
    "occasions": ["breakfast", "teatime", "brunch", "special_occasions", "baking_experiment"],
    "cultural_notes": "This recipe is a modern fusion that combines a classic British baking technique with a beloved Ugandan tropical fruit. Jackfruit (fenesi) is widely enjoyed in Uganda when in season, either eaten fresh or used in local dishes. Incorporating it into scones represents an innovative way to use a local ingredient in global recipes, celebrating Uganda's abundant produce in new forms."
  },
